The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE ALBUM

 (Rs 65)Fusing Indian and western classical music traditions, 

 the album features compositions by Ustad Amjad Ali Khan, 

 arranged and orchestrated by Violin Brothers Deb Sankar 

 Roy and Jyoti Sankar Roy. 

 THE WORKSHOP

 (Gurukul, 9 am-10.30 am, June 5-10, ) The workshop, to 

 introduce children to Hindustani vocal and instrumental 

 music, will cover the basic constituents like sur, tala, 

 laya, raga and rasa. To be conducted by AIR performers. 

 THE TV SHOW

 (Discovery 

 Channel, 8 pm, June 5) To mark World Environment Day, Discovery 

 Channel airs an hour-long package of four documentary films 

 on four distinct environment issues impacting India. The films 

 are Nila Madhab Panda?s Climate of Orphans, Sayed Fayaz?s 

 A Degree of Concern, Vijay Jodha?s The Weeping Apple 

 Tree and Geeta Singh?s A Green Agony . 




